        You are analyzing a 3D Slicer extension's cookbook workflow and must decompose
        each step into atomic sub-operations.

        ## Cookbook Steps
        Step 1: 1. If the fibula is from the right leg, tick the "Right side leg" checkbox.
Step 2: 2. In the "Select mandibular segmentation" section, choose the mandibular segmentation.
Step 3: 3. In the "Select fibula segmentation" section, choose the fibula segmentation.
Step 4: 4. For the "Current Scalar Volume" option, select the Mandible Volume.
Step 5: 5. Click "Create bone models from segmentations" button.
Step 6: 6. Change the layout to "Conventional".
Step 7: 7. For the R (red) view, toggle on "slice visibility in 3D view".
Step 8: 8. For the R (red) view, toggle on "FOV, Spacing match 2D" (adjusts slice resolution to match the 2D viewport pixel spacing).
Step 9: 9. In the toolbar, toggle on "slice intersection visibility. Hold Shift key and move mouse in a view to set slice intersection position." (Note it's not "crosshair visibility"), and set "slice intersection visibility" selected.
Step 10: 10. Manually adjust the slice intersection position.
Step 11: 11. Click the "Add mandibular curve" button.
Step 12: 12. In the Markups module's "Display" > "Advanced" panel, configure "View" to show in both "View 1" and "Red".
Step 13: 13. Manually click and draw on the "Red" view to create a curve along the mandible.
Step 14: 14. Restore the BoneReconstructionPlanner custom layout registered by the extension. This is a layout/view operation.
Step 15: 15. For the R (red) view, toggle off "slice visibility in 3D view".
Step 16: 16. Manually set how many cut planes you want.
Step 17: 17. Click "Add cut plane" button.
Step 18: 18. Place one mandibular cut plane using the extension's Add cut plane workflow. If the user requested N cut planes, repeat the Add cut plane + place plane
  interaction N times. Do not store these planes as a rotation plane; they are mandibular cut planes managed by the extension.
Step 19: 19. Click "Add fibula line" button.
Step 20: 20. Draw a line over the fibula in "3D View 2", starting with the first point distally and the last point proximally.
Step 21: 21. Click "Center fibula line using fibula model" button to align the line with the anatomical axis of the fibula.
Step 22: 22. Click "Update fibula planes over fibula line; update fibula bone pieces and transform them to mandible" to generate the reconstruction and create the fibula cut planes.

